\b #Version Dates#\b0\par
-----------------------------------------------------\par
11th October 2010: Released character as version 1.0\par
\par
-----------------------------------------------------\par
27th October 2010: Updated > 1.1\par
\par
1. You can now change the success rate of all super moves. \par
2. Many moves have been speeded up and have their damage increased a little.\par
\par
-----------------------------------------------------\par
12th January 2011: Updated > 1.2\par
\par
1. No more Winane's A.I.\par
2. Added special intro\par
3. Fixed the pallete issue. The palettes only worked on Winmugen before.\par
4. Hitting any shruiken other than the windmill one with a normal attack will create a clone of naruto. This has been fixed.\par
5. Naruto's japanese voice is here! However, it's in a separate file. To implement it, just replace the original .snd file within the character. Speaking of which, most of the voice sounds have been replaced to implement the above feature.\par
6. When Naruto gets his "Nine-tailed Fox" super countered, the full-screen effect of Naruto stays until the round ends or is restarted. This has been fixed.\par
7. Some supers actually give back some power when hitting the opponent with them. This has been fixed.\par
8. Fixed the debug flood issue that happens during any "Rasengan" based attack.\par
9. Fixed the "defeated" intro repeating issue that happened when naruto gets defeated on the first round, but wins the next round.\par
10. Updated only the successful "Rasengan" super: it now forms a giant ball that sends the opponent back!\par
11. Naruto now has a special intro againsed Sasuke by me as well.\par
12. A.I begins to attack before the round even starts. This has been fixed.\par
\par
-----------------------------------------------------\par
6th September 2011: Updated > 1.3\par
\par
1. You can now combo multiple weak attacks. The weak attacks that don't have much pushback now have a higher pushback.\par
2. The win quotes now only have the english language; it's too annoying to bother with the other languages. (Sorry)\par
3. You can now move during the super jump by holding forward or back while in the air.\par
4. "Windmill of Shadows". The windmill shruiken now hits the opponent and can be controlled, and it now stops when it hits the other side of the screen as well as waiting for it to produce the Naruto clone.\par
5. Any projectile thrown during the air version of "Ninja Tool Throw" can now hit opponents that are already down, but touching the floor will bring you down to your standing state.\par
6. Transitions between crouching and standing attacks (and vice-versa) are now easier to perform and can now chain between the two.\par
\par
-----------------------------------------------------\par
25th October 2012: Updated > 1.4\par
\par
1. "Windmill of Shadows". The windmill shruiken now hits the opponent and can be controlled, and it now stops when it hits the other side of the screen as well as waiting for it to produce the Naruto clone.\par
2. Any projectile thrown during the air version of "Ninja Tool Throw" can now hit opponents that are already down, but touching the floor will bring you down to your standing state. Also, you won't gain power unless you throw the projectile.\par
3. Transitions between crouching and standing attacks (and vice-versa) are now easier to perform and can now chain between the two.\par
4. Collisions of all types have been reduced by size and number considerably.\par
5. The log version of "Substitution Jutsu" now takes 500 power to perform, but is also suceptable to throws.\par
6. "Moon Kick" has less invincibility frames than before, and now prevents Naruto from standing in mid-air when hit while performing the move.\par
7. "Dash Slash" is now quicker to use for weaker versions.\par
8. Most super attacks are now easier to block.\par
9. Super-jumping is now easier to use effectively.\par
10. "Slashing Upper" is now scrapped.\par
11. Fixed an infinite with "Ninja Tool Throw", and a potential uber-damaging combo from the windmill shruiken.\par
\par
